<TITLE> Stocks open upbeat on power, banks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 03 (bdnews24.com)Dhaka stocks opened upbeat Thursday driven by power and banking sector shares. The market saw a steep decline in the general index at the opening, though it recovered losses after the first hour and continued to gain in the midday sessions. At 11.35 am, the benchmark DGEN or general index rose 8.78 points or 0.29 percent to 2968.14. The DSI or all share price index was at 2498.61, up 6.89 points or 0.27 percent. Turnover amounted to Tk 453.756 million from trading of 2,304,034 shares. Of the issues traded 112 gained, 48 lost and some 18 issues remained unchanged. Summit Power at 11.45 am headed the top share board by value, selling down at Tk 1374 from Wednesday's closing of Tk 1432.75 after the regulatory body disapproved the company's proposal to issue rights shares. AB Bank rose to Tk 2642 from Wednesday's Tk 2631.75. Market major Square Pharma gained slightly, after the previous day's decline, to Tk 3600 from Tk 3593.75. BRAC Bank also gained after falling the previous day, selling at Tk 1580 from Tk 1562.25. UCBL however fell to Tk 4135 from Tk 4159 the previous day. Among the other scrips on the top share board by value, IFIC, Prime Bank, Grameen1 MF gained. Trust Bank and Power Grid Company of Bangladesh
